AlaEServiceUNIProfileProtocolTreatment.name: AlaEServiceUNIProfileProtocolTreatment
AlaEServiceUNIProfileProtocolTreatment.description: The behavior of the bridge in regards to the given protocols packets received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the packets to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the packets to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol.

alcatelIND1EServiceMIBGroups.name: alcatelIND1EServiceMIBGroups
alcatelIND1EServiceMIBGroups.description: Branch For E-Service Units Of Conformance.

alaEServiceMode.name: alaEServiceMode
alaEServiceMode.description: The current mode configured for Vlan Stacking and Layer 2 tunnel configuration. legacyMode (1) indicates that the commands from AlcatelIND1VLANStacking.mib are to be used. eServiceMode (2) indicates the commands from this MIB are to be used.

alaEServiceSapProfileTable.name: alaEServiceSapProfileTable
alaEServiceSapProfileTable.description: A table that contains service profiles containing performance and control attributes. An entry in this table is created when a new service profile is defined.

alaEServiceSapProfileID.name: alaEServiceSapProfileID
alaEServiceSapProfileID.description: A label given to uniquely identify this profile. Must be at least one character long.

alaEServiceSapProfileCVLANTreatment.name: alaEServiceSapProfileCVLANTreatment
alaEServiceSapProfileCVLANTreatment.description: The type of VLAN stacking operation to be performed on a customer frame entering this service. Stack Svlan (1) indicates that the SVLAN is to be pre-pended on the frame before any existing 802.1Q tag. Translate (2) means to replace the existing 802.1Q tag with the SVLAN. Change CVLAN (3) indicates that the customer tag is to remain on the frame but its value is to be changed to the supplied value.

alaEServiceSapProfileReplacementCVLAN.name: alaEServiceSapProfileReplacementCVLAN
alaEServiceSapProfileReplacementCVLAN.description: The CVLAN ID to use when using the Change CVLAN treatment mode.

alaEServiceSapProfilePriorityMapMode.name: alaEServiceSapProfilePriorityMapMode
alaEServiceSapProfilePriorityMapMode.description: This object describes the source of the value for the priority field of the SVLAN 802.1Q tag when pre-pended to the customer data frame.NotAssigned(0), MapInnerPtoOuterP (1) uses the priority field of the incoming frame when tagged to fill in the priority field of the SVLAN tag. mapInnerDscpToOuterP (2) uses the frames priority bits in its IP DSCP field to fill in the priority field of the SVLAN tag. FixedP (3) uses the supplied FixedPriorityValue to fill in the SVLAN tag priority bits.

alaEServiceSapProfileFixedPriority.name: alaEServiceSapProfileFixedPriority
alaEServiceSapProfileFixedPriority.description: This object describes the value of the priority field of the 802.1Q SVLAN tag pre-pended to customer data frames when the fixed priority mapping mode is selected.

alaEServiceSapProfileIngressBW.name: alaEServiceSapProfileIngressBW
alaEServiceSapProfileIngressBW.description: This object describes this limit of ingress bandwidth for the traffic to which this profile is applied. If 0, no bandwidth limit is applied. This number represents traffic in units of 1,000,000 bits per second. Note that all CVLAN that belong to this SAP will share this aggregated limit.

alaEServiceSapProfileBandwidthShare.name: alaEServiceSapProfileBandwidthShare
alaEServiceSapProfileBandwidthShare.description: This object describes the use of the bandwidth limit in how it is applied across multiple ports of the SAP. If set to notApplicable(0), the SAP is not used. If set to Shared (1), all the ports that are part of the SAP will use aggregated bandwidth, sharing some part of the bandwidth limit. If set to notShared (2), each port will use its own bandwidth meter for this SAP. This value is not used if ingressBandwidth is 0.

alaEServiceSapProfileRowStatus.name: alaEServiceSapProfileRowStatus
alaEServiceSapProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

alaEServiceSapProfileEgressBW.name: alaEServiceSapProfileEgressBW
alaEServiceSapProfileEgressBW.description: This object describes this limit of egress bandwidth for each UNI of the SAP to which this profile is applied. If 0, no bandwidth limit is applied. This number represents traffic in units of Megabits per second. Note that all CVLAN that belong to this SAP will share this aggregated limit.

alaEServiceUNIProfileTable.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileTable
alaEServiceUNIProfileTable.description: A table that contains service profiles containing performance and control attributes. An entry in this table is created when a new service profile is defined.

alaEServiceUNIProfileID.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileID
alaEServiceUNIProfileID.description: A label given to uniquely identify this profile. Must be at least one character long.

alaEServiceUNIProfileStpBpduTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileStpBpduTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfileStpBpduTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the spanning tree protocol BPDU received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currnetly Peer is not supported for Spanning Tree

alaEServiceUNIProfile8021xTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfile8021xTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfile8021xTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the IEEE 802.1x PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currnetly only drop is supported

alaEServiceUNIProfile8021ABTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfile8021ABTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfile8021ABTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the IEEE 802.1AB PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currently only drop is supported

alaEServiceUNIProfile8023adTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfile8023adTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfile8023adTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the IEEE 802.1ad PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currently only peer is supported

alaEServiceUNIProfileGvrpTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileGvrpTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfileGvrpTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the GVRP PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currently peer is not supported for GVRP

alaEServiceUNIProfileAmapTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileAmapTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfileAmapTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the Alcatel propietary AMAP PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currently drop is only supported

alaEServiceUNIProfileMvrpTreatment.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileMvrpTreatment
alaEServiceUNIProfileMvrpTreatment.description: This object describes the behavior of the bridge in regards to the MVRP PDU frames received on the UNI. Tunnel (1) enables the PDU to be tunneled across the provider network. Discard (2) causes the PDU of the protocol to be discarded and not enter the provider network. Peer (3) means that on this port the bridge is to participate in the protocol. Currently peer is not supported for MVRP

alaEServiceUNIProfileRowStatus.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileRowStatus
alaEServiceUNIProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

alaEServiceTable.name: alaEServiceTable
alaEServiceTable.description: A table that contains the services and their assigned SVLAN for the E-Service feature.

alaEServiceID.name: alaEServiceID
alaEServiceID.description: A label given to uniquely identify this Service. Must be at least one character long.

alaEServiceSVLAN.name: alaEServiceSVLAN
alaEServiceSVLAN.description: The SVLAN number of the SVLAN chosen to the be transport for this service.

alaEServiceVlanType.name: alaEServiceVlanType
alaEServiceVlanType.description: The type of the vlan this service is going to attach to. When creating the service, the type should match the vlanId specified in the request.

alaEServiceRowStatus.name: alaEServiceRowStatus
alaEServiceRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a service. When creating or deleting the service, the user needs to provide both the svlan and the vlantype objects.

alaEServiceSapTable.name: alaEServiceSapTable
alaEServiceSapTable.description: A table that contains the Service Access Points (Sap) listed by ID. This table is used to create, delete, and modify the SAP's profile

alaEServiceSapID.name: alaEServiceSapID
alaEServiceSapID.description: A Number given to uniquely identify the SAP.

alaEServiceSapServiceID.name: alaEServiceSapServiceID
alaEServiceSapServiceID.description: A label given to uniquely identify the Service this SAP is for. Must be at least one character long.

alaEServiceSapProfile.name: alaEServiceSapProfile
alaEServiceSapProfile.description: The string identifying the SAP Profile this sap is to use. If specified, must match an existing SAP Profile.

alaEServiceSapRowStatus.name: alaEServiceSapRowStatus
alaEServiceSapRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a sap. When creating the sap, the user needs to provide the service name in the same set request.

alaEServiceSapCvlanTable.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanTable
alaEServiceSapCvlanTable.description: A table that contains the Service Access Points (Sap) where the CVLANs are bound to their service.

alaEServiceSapCvlanSapID.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanSapID
alaEServiceSapCvlanSapID.description: A Number given to uniquely identify this SAP.

alaEServiceSapCvlanCvlan.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanCvlan
alaEServiceSapCvlanCvlan.description: This object is the CVLAN ID that this binding is targeted at. The CVLAN ID may be 0, which indicates an all or untagged only mapping type.

alaEServiceSapCvlanMapType.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanMapType
alaEServiceSapCvlanMapType.description: This object is the mapping type that defines what CVLANs are mapped into this service. Multiple mappings can be defined for CVLAN to service, however only one all (2) or untaggedOnly (3) mapping entry can be created per UNI. A mapping type of Single (1) denotes a specific CVLAN value to bind to the service. A mapping type of All (2) denotes that all customer frames that do not map to any other SAP, will be mapped into this service. A mapping type of Untagged (3) denotes that only the untagged frames will be mapped into this service.

alaEServiceSapCvlanRowStatus.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanRowStatus
alaEServiceSapCvlanRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a SAP.

alaEServicePortTable.name: alaEServicePortTable
alaEServicePortTable.description: A table that contains the ports used by the EService feature. Both UNI and NNI are listed here.

alaEServicePortEntry.name: alaEServicePortEntry
alaEServicePortEntry.description: The list of ports being used by EService.

alaEServicePortID.name: alaEServicePortID
alaEServicePortID.description: The IfIndex of this UNI or NNI Port.

alaEServicePortType.name: alaEServicePortType
alaEServicePortType.description: The type of port for Vlan Stacking operation. uni (1) represents a customer facing port on which traffic may enter the E-Service. nni (2) respresents a provider network port over which the E-Service may be connected.

alaEServicePortVendorTpid.name: alaEServicePortVendorTpid
alaEServicePortVendorTpid.description: he TPID for this port if type is NNI. It is used for the incoming data traffic parsing and it is substituted to the 802.1Q standard Tpid for the outgoing data traffic. This is used for compatibility with other vendor equipment. The default value is the standard value 0x8100.

alaEServicePortLegacyStpBpdu.name: alaEServicePortLegacyStpBpdu
alaEServicePortLegacyStpBpdu.description: The legacy STP BPDU treatment for this port if NNI. It defines the type of processing applied to STP legacy BPDUs on network ports. Legacy BPDU refer to conventional/customer BPDUs with MAC address 01:80:c2:00:00:00 and its processing on network ports can be enabled/disabled by this object.By default the value is disabled i.e provider MAC BPDU with MAC address 01:80:c2:00:00:08 would be processed at network ports.

alaEServicePortLegacyGvrpPdu.name: alaEServicePortLegacyGvrpPdu
alaEServicePortLegacyGvrpPdu.description: The legacy GVRP PDU treatment for this port if NNI. It defines the type of processing applied to GVRP PDUs on network ports.

alaEServicePortUniProfile.name: alaEServicePortUniProfile
alaEServicePortUniProfile.description: The label of an existing UNI profile that which contains various properties to be applied to this port if UNI.

alaEServicePortTransBridging.name: alaEServicePortTransBridging
alaEServicePortTransBridging.description: The Transparent Bridging status for the nni Port.

alaEServicePortLegacyMvrpPdu.name: alaEServicePortLegacyMvrpPdu
alaEServicePortLegacyMvrpPdu.description: The legacy MVRP PDU treatment for this port if NNI. It defines the type of processing applied to MVRP PDUs on network ports.

alaEServicePortRowStatus.name: alaEServicePortRowStatus
alaEServicePortRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a binding

alaEServiceSapUniTable.name: alaEServiceSapUniTable
alaEServiceSapUniTable.description: A table that contains the UNI that are bound to each SAP for classifying traffic into each EService. Not that writing to this table may create a new UNI.

alaEServiceSapUniEntry.name: alaEServiceSapUniEntry
alaEServiceSapUniEntry.description: The list of SAP-UNI bindings being used by EService.

alaEServiceSapUniSap.name: alaEServiceSapUniSap
alaEServiceSapUniSap.description: The SAP ID that is configured onto this port.

alaEServiceSapUniUni.name: alaEServiceSapUniUni
alaEServiceSapUniUni.description: The IfIndex of this UNI Port.

alaEServiceSapUniRowStatus.name: alaEServiceSapUniRowStatus
alaEServiceSapUniRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a binding

alaEServiceNniSvlanTable.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanTable
alaEServiceNniSvlanTable.description: A table that contains the SVLANs bound to each NNI for use by the EService feature.

alaEServiceNniSvlanEntry.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanEntry
alaEServiceNniSvlanEntry.description: The list of NNI-SVLAN bindings being used by EService.

alaEServiceNniSvlanNni.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanNni
alaEServiceNniSvlanNni.description: The IfIndex of this NNI Port.

alaEServiceNniSvlanSvlan.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanSvlan
alaEServiceNniSvlanSvlan.description: The SVLAN bound to this port. SVLAN cannot be 1.

alaEServiceNniSvlanRowStatus.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanRowStatus
alaEServiceNniSvlanRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The supported value for set are createAndGo (4) and destroy(6), to add or remove a binding

alaEServiceNniSvlanVpaType.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanVpaType
alaEServiceNniSvlanVpaType.description: The object is used to specify whether the VPA state is to be controlled by an ERP or a STP. By default VPA state is controlled by STP.

alaEServiceSapProfileGroup.name: alaEServiceSapProfileGroup
alaEServiceSapProfileGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service Sap Profiles.

alaEServiceUNIProfileGroup.name: alaEServiceUNIProfileGroup
alaEServiceUNIProfileGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of EService UNI Profiles.

alaEServiceGroup.name: alaEServiceGroup
alaEServiceGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Services.

alaEServiceSapGroup.name: alaEServiceSapGroup
alaEServiceSapGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service SAPs.

alaEServiceSapCvlanGroup.name: alaEServiceSapCvlanGroup
alaEServiceSapCvlanGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service SAP CVLAN bindings.

alaEServicePortGroup.name: alaEServicePortGroup
alaEServicePortGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service Ports.

alaEServiceSapUniGroup.name: alaEServiceSapUniGroup
alaEServiceSapUniGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service SAP to UNI Binding.

alaEServiceNniSvlanGroup.name: alaEServiceNniSvlanGroup
alaEServiceNniSvlanGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service SVLAN to NNI Binding.

alaEServiceInfoGroup.name: alaEServiceInfoGroup
alaEServiceInfoGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of E-Service Info Binding.
